  "texts": [
    "Composing with the isomorphism of Theorem 3.5, this defines a map Φ, *Σ C: C * (Σ C) → A(Σ C), with Φ, * Σ C α ⊗ w 0 ⊗ • • • ⊗ w m:= Φ Σ C ((id X 0 ⊗ α) • coev X 0) ⊗ w 0 ⊗ • • • ⊗ w m (32) for any α ∈ Z(C)(X * 0 → X 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ X m), and any boundary conditionsw κ ∈ C(X κ → χ ⊗S κ) for κ = 0, • • •, m.Combined with the isomorphism of Theorem 4.4, H C ≃ A(Σ C), this gives: Proposition 4.6.",
    "Let C be a finite connected region and let be an anchor for C. Then the mapΨ C:= σ -1 C • Φ, * C: C * (Σ C) → H C (33)is a unitary isomorphism of A(∂Σ C)-modules.We can now characterise the spaces D C (p) as follows:Lemma 4.7.",
    "Let C be a finite region and let p = {p S } S∈Bd(Σ C) with each p S either a minimal projector of type X S ∈ Irr Z(C), or a maximally mixed boundary condition ⋆ X S of type X S. Let be an anchor for C. Then D C (p) is isomorphic to the space of density matrices onZ(C)(X * S 0 → m κ=1 X S κ).Proof: If each p S is a minimal projector of type X S, then Proposition 4.6 yields an isomorphism,H C (p) Ψ C ≃ Z(C)(X S 0 → m κ=1 X S κ),and the claim follows.Let us now consider the case with one maximally mixed boundary condition p S * = ⋆ X S * and all other p S given by minimal projections of types X S. Proposition 4.6 yields an isomorphism of Tube-modulesH C (p) Ψ C ≃ Z(C)(X * S 0 → m κ=1 X S κ) ⊗ C(X S * → χ ⊗S *).Density matrices ρ ∈ D C (p) are supported on H C (p) and therefore in one-to-one correspondence with density matricesρ ′ = Ψ C | H C (p) -1 ρ Ψ C | H C (p) acting on Z(C)(X * S 0 → m κ=1 X S κ) ⊗ C(X S * → χ ⊗S *).The algebra Tube S * acts on the latter space by arbitrary unitaries of the form 1 ⊗ U since the representation on C(X S * → χ ⊗S *) is irreducible.",
    "The maximally mixed boundary condition ⋆ X S * asserts that ρ ′ commutes with all unitaries of this form.",
    "This implies that ρ ′ = σ ⊗ 1 for a density matrix σ supported on the space Z(C)(X * S 0 → m κ=1 X S κ)."
